    • Enum Constant Detail

      • AUTHORISATION_FAILED

        public static final PumpState AUTHORISATION_FAILED
        Failed to Authorise the pump. This state is currently not used and will be available in a future version of the API.

      • AUTHORISING

        public static final PumpState AUTHORISING
        The pump is being Authorised. If authorisation is successful its state will change to the DELIVERY_STARTING state.

      • BUSY

        public static final PumpState BUSY
        Pump temporarily unavailable.

        Note : This state normally indicates the pump is being prepared for operation by The Enabler, so usually occurs just after a pump comes online.

      • CALLING

        public static final PumpState CALLING
        Pump is asking for authorisation.

        Note : This is either a compulsory authorise or has a current transaction that cannot be automatically stacked.

      • DELIVERING

        public static final PumpState DELIVERING
        Pump has been authorised and is currently delivering.
        See Also:
        Pump.isFuelFlow()

      • DELIVERY_FINISHED

        public static final PumpState DELIVERY_FINISHED
        Pump has just completed a delivery and will remain in this state until Enabler determines if a delivery has been made.

      • DELIVERY_PAUSED

        public static final PumpState DELIVERY_PAUSED
        Pump was PAUSED while it was delivering.

      • DELIVERY_STOPPED

        public static final PumpState DELIVERY_STOPPED
        Pump was stopped during a delivery. The delivery cannot be resumed after beging stopped.

      • ERROR

        public static final PumpState ERROR
        Pump is in error

      • LOCKED

        public static final PumpState LOCKED
        Pump is idle, nozzle in.

      • MANUAL_PUMP

        public static final PumpState MANUAL_PUMP
        This pump is a non automated or not connected pump type and is present so that transactions can be manually logged against it. Pumps of this type will stay in this state.

      • NOT_ALLOWED

        public static final PumpState NOT_ALLOWED
        Authorisation is not allowed for the Hose that has been lifted because the products specified in the Authorisation are not available on the hose

      • NOT_INSTALLED

        public static final PumpState NOT_INSTALLED
        Pump is not installed

        Note : This most commonly occurs when a pump is linked to a Enabler Port which has the protocol set to NOT_INSTALLED.

      • NOT_RESPONDING

        public static final PumpState NOT_RESPONDING
        Pump is not currently communicating with The Enabler
